They show that magnetic fields never exist as isolated poles, while electric fields arise directly from the presence of charge. They also reveal that a changing magnetic field creates an electric field, forming the basis of electromagnetic induction. 

Similarly, they explain that electric currents, along with time-varying electric fields, generate magnetic fields. Taken as a unified framework, Maxwellâs equations demonstrate that electricity and magnetism are deeply interconnected and naturally give rise to electromagnetic waves, which include visible light, radio waves, and all forms of communication signals in modern technology.
